Part D: Real-World Word Problems

Show your work.

A class is printing 986 pages for a project. Each printer tray holds 45 pages. How many full trays can they fill, and how many pages are left over?

A farmer collects 18,560 apples and packs them into crates of 32. How many crates does he fill?

A school has 1,245 students. They are placed into groups of 9 for an activity. How many groups are formed?

A store orders 3 shipments of 4,728 stickers each. How many stickers does the store receive in total?

Part E: Challenge Problems

Explain your reasoning.

A number is multiplied by 6, then divided by 3. How does the final value compare to the original number?

A student has 1,000 coins. After sorting them evenly into bags of 8, how many bags will be filled? What will happen to any leftover coins?